1
00:00:01,050 --> 00:00:02,890
Previously on Fairy Tail:

2
00:00:02,890 --> 00:00:04,800
Scary Lucy is back!

3
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:07,740
On the inside, Scary Lucy isn't 
so different than the real one.

4
00:00:07,740 --> 00:00:09,940
Stop calling us "scary" 
or "real" all the time!

5
00:00:09,940 --> 00:00:12,360
When you line three of them 
up, it's seriously freaky.

6
00:00:12,360 --> 00:00:13,680
That's just mean!

7
00:00:13,680 --> 00:00:16,560
What about if the three of them 
combine into a Giant Lucy?!

8
00:00:16,560 --> 00:00:18,780
They'd be the enemy of all humanity!

9
00:00:18,780 --> 00:00:22,580
Grr! Can we get on with the story now?

10
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:05,270
I-I'm sorry! I don't know!

11
00:02:09,980 --> 00:02:10,430
Huh?

12
00:02:11,450 --> 00:02:13,710
Are you really the me from before?

13
00:02:13,710 --> 00:02:18,320
Y-Yes! I'm always told that my personality 
changes when I get behind the wheel...

14
00:02:18,650 --> 00:02:21,450
This is the real Edo Natsu!

15
00:02:23,110 --> 00:02:24,540
Please don't yell!

16
00:02:25,010 --> 00:02:26,300
It's scary...

17
00:02:30,200 --> 00:02:32,560
Wanna try doing a mirror act together?

18
00:02:35,530 --> 00:02:37,350
Welcome Home!

19
00:02:39,340 --> 00:02:40,970
I'm sorry! I'm sorry!

20
00:02:41,420 --> 00:02:43,530
B-But I can't!

21
00:02:44,960 --> 00:02:48,330
I just came this far 
because Lucy-san asked me!

22
00:02:49,030 --> 00:02:51,760
It's okay. You don't have to force yourself.

23
00:02:55,450 --> 00:02:58,150
Yeah, and it doesn't seem like 
you'd be much help anyway.

24
00:02:58,740 --> 00:02:59,590
Carla!

25
00:03:02,290 --> 00:03:04,400
Are you, perhaps, Wendy-san?

26
00:03:05,300 --> 00:03:05,710
Yes.

27
00:03:07,490 --> 00:03:08,800
You're all small and cute!

28
00:03:09,330 --> 00:03:10,970
And you, sir, are the me from Earthland?

29
00:03:11,300 --> 00:03:12,960
Who're you callin' sir?

30
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:16,200
I'm Happy, and that's Carla.

31
00:03:17,810 --> 00:03:20,590
And I'm... Well, I think you know by now.

32
00:03:21,450 --> 00:03:23,830
I'm sorry! I'll do whatever you say!

33
00:03:25,450 --> 00:03:28,890
Take it a little easier on 
me over there, would ya?

34
00:03:29,780 --> 00:03:36,630
Our Lucy-san told me to carry you 
all here, and that's why I did it...

35
00:03:37,970 --> 00:03:38,810
T-That's...

36
00:03:39,700 --> 00:03:41,220
Is that the Royal City?

37
00:03:41,770 --> 00:03:43,010
Oh, how pretty!

38
00:03:43,320 --> 00:03:45,990
Wait, what? If we've arrived, 
tell us that in the first place!

39
00:03:46,850 --> 00:03:48,050
I'm so sorry!

40
00:03:57,350 --> 00:04:00,730
Great! I didn't think 
we'd get here this early!

41
00:04:01,340 --> 00:04:04,310
Somewhere down there is the lacrima 
that they turned everyone into.

42
00:04:05,060 --> 00:04:06,290
Let's hurry up and go!

43
00:04:07,600 --> 00:04:08,660
Hold it, Carla!

44
00:04:09,320 --> 00:04:10,670
Thanks!

45
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:12,240
Give my regards to me!

46
00:04:12,700 --> 00:04:17,500
U-Um... Are you really... 
going to fight the Kingdom?

47
00:04:17,940 --> 00:04:21,820
I don't know. As long as we can rescue 
our friends, that's all I care about.

48
00:04:22,530 --> 00:04:27,450
But if they aren't gonna return 'em so 
easily, then we got no other choice than to fight!

49
00:04:39,850 --> 00:04:42,690
There's no winning against the Kingdom.

50
00:05:04,250 --> 00:05:05,440
What is this?

51
00:05:05,610 --> 00:05:09,410
This is surprising. I thought the 
Kingdom was ruled by a dictator, so...

52
00:05:10,360 --> 00:05:13,080
I expected the city to be more run-down.

53
00:05:13,530 --> 00:05:15,920
Plus, we got into the city no prob.

54
00:05:17,500 --> 00:05:19,420
This place is totally different 
than Louen and Sycca.

55
00:05:19,910 --> 00:05:20,790
It's like an amusement park.

56
00:05:21,470 --> 00:05:24,420
They steal magic power and collect 
it here in the Royal City.

57
00:05:24,890 --> 00:05:28,530
They created this pleasure-town to 
gain popularity with the citizens.

58
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:31,400
This King's got a screw loose.

59
00:05:33,370 --> 00:05:35,820
It looks like something's 
going on over there.

60
00:05:39,070 --> 00:05:40,940
Are they having a parade or something?

61
00:05:40,940 --> 00:05:42,880
Let's go check it out!

62
00:05:42,880 --> 00:05:44,230
Aye, sir!

63
00:05:44,230 --> 00:05:47,110
We didn't come here to play, you people!

64
00:05:48,250 --> 00:05:49,400
What is it? What is sit?

65
00:05:49,400 --> 00:05:50,850
Wait, Natsu!

66
00:05:52,630 --> 00:05:54,640
What a huge crowd of people!

67
00:05:55,270 --> 00:05:56,310
Sheesh...

68
00:05:58,300 --> 00:06:01,080
Hey, don't just stop like that!

69
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:13,470
A-A lacrima?

70
00:06:14,270 --> 00:06:16,560
Could... that be...

71
00:06:17,250 --> 00:06:18,930
Everyone from Magnolia...

72
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:21,400
Plus, there's a chunk that's been removed.

73
00:06:21,870 --> 00:06:23,650
There are marks that show 
a piece has been cut off.

74
00:06:24,870 --> 00:06:26,250
That's not all of it?

75
00:07:14,570 --> 00:07:17,000
Children of Edolas!

76
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:24,070
Our blessed land of Edolas has used Anima to 
call forth ten years' worth of magic power!

77
00:07:25,130 --> 00:07:29,600
Call forth, my butt! He 
stole it from our world!

78
00:07:29,900 --> 00:07:31,600
Stay calm, he-cat.

79
00:07:32,400 --> 00:07:36,290
Everyone, sing a song! 
Everyone, laugh out loud!

80
00:07:36,290 --> 00:07:39,270
Let us raise up our voices 
together in jubilation!

81
00:07:49,620 --> 00:07:54,350
This magic power belongs jointly 
to the citizens of Edolas!

82
00:07:54,350 --> 00:07:59,400
Also, only the citizens of Edolas are the 
race blessed with inheriting the future!

83
00:08:00,120 --> 00:08:04,710
No one will steal magic 
power from our kingdom!

84
00:08:07,840 --> 00:08:13,720
And I promise to obtain 
even greater magic power!

85
00:08:14,960 --> 00:08:19,220
Enough to make this pittance of 
magic seem like mere garbage!

86
00:08:36,810 --> 00:08:40,390
Edolas! Edolas!

87
00:08:40,740 --> 00:08:44,280
Edolas! Edolas!

88
00:08:46,070 --> 00:08:47,670
Hmph. How stupid.

89
00:08:48,050 --> 00:08:52,450
You can manipulate that many 
people with such a flimsy speech?

90
00:08:54,720 --> 00:08:57,470
What will I do now?

91
00:09:05,450 --> 00:09:06,480
Keep control of yourself!

92
00:09:07,310 --> 00:09:08,340
I can't!

93
00:09:08,990 --> 00:09:11,150
That... That lacrima is...

94
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:14,450
Please!

95
00:09:15,750 --> 00:09:17,820
Everyone feels the same way, so...

96
00:09:22,700 --> 00:09:24,200
Okay, Natsu?

97
00:10:01,010 --> 00:10:02,830
Yeah, I can't take it any more.

98
00:10:04,100 --> 00:10:05,820
We'll charge into the castle!

99
00:10:05,820 --> 00:10:07,360
Wait a little more.

100
00:10:07,810 --> 00:10:08,790
What for?

101
00:10:09,650 --> 00:10:13,060
We have to make a plan, or we'll 
never return everyone to normal.

102
00:10:15,940 --> 00:10:21,670
Everyone's been turned into that crystal. 
How can we turn them back, I wonder?

103
00:10:24,710 --> 00:10:26,730
We have no choice but to 
ask the King directly.

104
00:10:27,400 --> 00:10:29,210
There's no way he'd just tell us!

105
00:10:29,420 --> 00:10:31,100
Then we should hit him until he does!

106
00:10:31,850 --> 00:10:36,520
I see! The King knows how 
to bring everyone back?

107
00:10:36,720 --> 00:10:37,420
Perhaps.

108
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:42,320
This might work! If I can just 
get close enough to him...

109
00:10:42,560 --> 00:10:43,370
Really?

110
00:10:44,090 --> 00:10:45,690
What are you talking about?

111
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:46,950
Gemini!

112
00:10:47,590 --> 00:10:50,200
Gemini can transform into anyone they touch,

113
00:10:50,200 --> 00:10:53,500
and while they're transformed they 
can also know what that person knew.

114
00:10:53,500 --> 00:10:58,150
In other words, if they can transform into 
the King, we might learn a way to save everyone!

115
00:10:59,350 --> 00:11:02,080
However, they can only 
transform for 5 minutes.

116
00:11:02,080 --> 00:11:05,400
Plus, the amount of transformations they 
can keep in stock is limited to two people.

117
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:10,230
If they transform into someone else, then 
the oldest one can't be used anymore.

118
00:11:12,150 --> 00:11:15,840
The question is just, how 
do we get close to the King?

119
00:11:16,650 --> 00:11:20,050
There are too many guards. 
We won't be able to easily.

120
00:11:20,850 --> 00:11:22,750
There is a way to get close to the King.

121
00:11:24,900 --> 00:11:28,860
It was originally a tunnel to allow the King 
to escape from the castle to outside the city.

122
00:11:29,170 --> 00:11:32,790
So there should be a way to get from outside 
the city to the basement of the castle.

123
00:11:33,330 --> 00:11:35,460
Wow! How do you know this?

124
00:11:35,910 --> 00:11:38,840
It's information... Fragments 
keep popping into my head.

125
00:11:40,990 --> 00:11:45,560
Since coming to Edolas, I've gained little 
bits of information about the land.

126
00:11:46,770 --> 00:11:48,430
I haven't at all.

127
00:11:49,140 --> 00:11:52,670
Anyway, if we can sneak into the castle 
like that, we'll be able to manage somehow!

128
00:11:52,670 --> 00:11:55,950
All right! Let's turn 
everyone back to normal!

129
00:11:55,950 --> 00:11:56,590
Right!

130
00:11:56,590 --> 00:11:57,480
Aye, sir!

131
00:11:57,790 --> 00:11:58,400
Wait.

132
00:11:58,710 --> 00:11:59,980
What is it this time?

133
00:12:00,650 --> 00:12:02,200
We leave tonight.

134
00:12:02,200 --> 00:12:04,660
Let's rest as much as we can for now.

135
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:49,650
The entrance to the tunnel should 
almost be in front of us.

136
00:12:56,810 --> 00:12:57,440
Is this it?

137
00:12:58,100 --> 00:12:59,530
Yes, definitely it.

138
00:12:59,950 --> 00:13:00,830
Great!

139
00:13:01,130 --> 00:13:01,710
Wait.

140
00:13:02,560 --> 00:13:04,000
Again?!

141
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:06,450
I understand your impatience, but stay calm.

142
00:13:07,160 --> 00:13:09,050
We can't go anywhere without light.

143
00:13:09,360 --> 00:13:13,680
Just leave that... to me!

144
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:21,300
See? You forgot. We can't use magic now.

145
00:13:27,650 --> 00:13:30,290
Lucy's the only one who can use magic.

146
00:13:30,290 --> 00:13:32,440
Yeah, I'm not feeling so 
confident about that...

147
00:13:32,440 --> 00:13:34,540
Well <i>soooorrrry</i> for not giving 
you enough confidence.

148
00:13:35,080 --> 00:13:36,600
Oops, did you hear that?

149
00:13:37,750 --> 00:13:39,500
Lucy-san, is that...

150
00:13:42,590 --> 00:13:43,760
Torches!

151
00:13:45,080 --> 00:13:46,590
I picked 'em up from over there!

152
00:13:47,670 --> 00:13:50,800
I've already wrapped them in 
cloth and soaked them in oil,

153
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:52,670
so all we need to do is 
light them and we're set.

154
00:13:53,100 --> 00:13:55,720
But, what about fire?

155
00:13:59,510 --> 00:14:02,520
Why do I have to do something like this?

156
00:14:02,520 --> 00:14:04,030
We don't have any choice!

157
00:14:04,030 --> 00:14:07,900
Consider it your chance to see what it's 
like being someone who can't use fire magic!

158
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:13,800
The ancient people were pretty amazing, 
making fire by doing things like this.

159
00:14:14,150 --> 00:14:14,790
Yeah.

160
00:14:18,510 --> 00:14:19,620
Not even close...

161
00:14:21,470 --> 00:14:22,450
I got it!

162
00:14:23,430 --> 00:14:24,150
Amazing!

163
00:14:24,150 --> 00:14:25,250
All right!

164
00:14:25,250 --> 00:14:26,940
You go, Lucy!

165
00:14:27,540 --> 00:14:30,200
And why can't you handle it?

166
00:14:30,340 --> 00:14:32,810
Who cares? As long as one of us made it...

167
00:14:36,110 --> 00:14:36,930
All right!

168
00:14:38,350 --> 00:14:39,720
I did it!

169
00:14:40,100 --> 00:14:41,290
All right!

170
00:14:43,550 --> 00:14:46,230
I'm exhausted before we 
even enter the tunnel!

171
00:14:51,030 --> 00:14:52,110
What is it?

172
00:14:54,400 --> 00:14:57,590
Oh, I get it. If you eat 
fire, then just maybe...

173
00:14:58,250 --> 00:15:00,020
So you think you can handle magic now?

174
00:15:00,810 --> 00:15:01,580
So?

175
00:15:06,830 --> 00:15:08,510
This part of me got all warm.

176
00:15:08,860 --> 00:15:10,630
Does that feel like Magic?

177
00:15:10,920 --> 00:15:11,980
Feeling?

178
00:15:12,850 --> 00:15:14,480
It might be!

179
00:15:14,480 --> 00:15:16,030
Ooh, neat!

180
00:15:16,400 --> 00:15:19,860
Give 'er a whirl! The Iron Fist 
of the Fire Dragon, reborn!

181
00:15:22,400 --> 00:15:24,270
Go!

182
00:15:28,940 --> 00:15:29,690
No use...

183
00:15:30,910 --> 00:15:33,360
You're just struggling pointlessly.

184
00:15:35,350 --> 00:15:38,350
I thought I could use magic 
by eating the fire here!

185
00:15:38,350 --> 00:15:42,580
Well, as long as I have 
my torch, we'll be fine!

186
00:15:42,580 --> 00:15:44,090
Don't get carried away.

187
00:15:52,150 --> 00:15:54,220
It doesn't seem like it's 
been used for a long time.

188
00:16:02,820 --> 00:16:04,350
Light up ahead of here!

189
00:16:17,110 --> 00:16:17,820
This is it.

190
00:16:20,320 --> 00:16:23,800
It's quite thick. Plus, it's 
been coated with magic.

191
00:16:23,800 --> 00:16:25,400
We can't get through that.

192
00:16:25,400 --> 00:16:29,610
But I'm correct. There should be 
another escape exit around here.

193
00:16:29,950 --> 00:16:31,390
We have to break through it, then...

194
00:16:31,870 --> 00:16:33,200
We have a way!

195
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:35,680
This is a perfect job for me!

196
00:16:38,550 --> 00:16:40,440
Gate of the Golden Bull, I open thee!

197
00:16:40,860 --> 00:16:41,690
Taurus!

198
00:16:48,670 --> 00:16:50,400
Right! Taurus can do it!

199
00:16:50,400 --> 00:16:54,800
Taurus has the most power out 
of all the spirits I command.

200
00:16:55,380 --> 00:16:57,410
He should totally be able 
to break down that wall.

201
00:16:57,410 --> 00:17:00,950
If that is what will do you good, I'll do it!

202
00:17:01,320 --> 00:17:02,740
Do a number on that wall!

203
00:17:03,230 --> 00:17:04,830
Here I come!

204
00:17:13,690 --> 00:17:15,490
Whoa!

205
00:17:15,490 --> 00:17:17,380
Oh, that wasn't much...

206
00:17:21,670 --> 00:17:22,340
Look!

207
00:17:22,600 --> 00:17:23,700
There's a path!

208
00:17:24,490 --> 00:17:27,630
Your information was right, Carla!

209
00:17:28,550 --> 00:17:31,060
That was a cinch, Lucy-san!

210
00:17:31,510 --> 00:17:33,240
Thank you, Taurus!

211
00:17:33,240 --> 00:17:35,710
That's it?

212
00:17:35,710 --> 00:17:37,860
What?

213
00:17:37,860 --> 00:17:41,290
If you're really grateful, you 
can show it by giving me a...

214
00:17:41,920 --> 00:17:44,150
Please stop leering at me like that.

215
00:17:48,910 --> 00:17:51,900
This should connect straight to the 
basement of the castle, I hope...

216
00:17:52,790 --> 00:17:56,270
The information was correct, 
so I'm sure it's right ahead.

217
00:17:59,420 --> 00:18:00,310
What's wrong, Happy?

218
00:18:01,700 --> 00:18:05,600
So, why don't I have any 
information, do you think?

219
00:18:08,520 --> 00:18:15,030
I'm a cat from Edolas, sent to Earthland 
with some kind of mission, just like you, right?

220
00:18:15,360 --> 00:18:17,500
You promised not to talk 
about that, remember?

221
00:18:18,470 --> 00:18:18,880
Aye.

222
00:18:20,290 --> 00:18:23,700
I don't know about a case like yours, either.

223
00:18:25,100 --> 00:18:27,160
Anyway, let's go further in.

224
00:18:27,640 --> 00:18:28,040
Yes.

225
00:18:28,250 --> 00:18:28,780
Yeah.

226
00:18:35,450 --> 00:18:37,090
Looks like the place is about to collapse.

227
00:18:37,600 --> 00:18:39,400
Don't jinx it, sheesh!

228
00:18:39,910 --> 00:18:42,480
But this really is an ancient tunnel...

229
00:18:42,480 --> 00:18:44,500
I wonder if there are ghosts and stuff?

230
00:18:47,610 --> 00:18:50,130
W-What is it, Natsu? Is 
there something there?

231
00:18:50,400 --> 00:18:52,300
Hold this.

232
00:18:52,300 --> 00:18:55,240
W-W-W-What?

233
00:18:55,240 --> 00:18:56,740
Don't move now.

234
00:19:00,030 --> 00:19:02,500
This is my territory!

235
00:19:06,850 --> 00:19:09,180
This is no time for playing around!

236
00:19:10,750 --> 00:19:12,400
This one is next.

237
00:19:13,100 --> 00:19:14,850
Left up there.

238
00:19:16,060 --> 00:19:17,430
Turn up there.

239
00:19:27,860 --> 00:19:30,050
We've come out to a pretty open place.

240
00:19:30,050 --> 00:19:33,650
It looks like this is where it connects 
to the basement of the castle.

241
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:37,520
I'm not sure how you did it, but 
you really saved the day, Carla!

242
00:19:37,950 --> 00:19:39,790
I don't know, either.

243
00:19:39,790 --> 00:19:42,190
Information just keeps popping into my head.

244
00:19:42,190 --> 00:19:43,870
Thank you, Carla.

245
00:19:43,870 --> 00:19:46,530
If you want to thank me, do 
it after we rescue everyone.

246
00:19:47,050 --> 00:19:48,880
Now is when things get difficult.

247
00:19:48,880 --> 00:19:53,040
We have to get to the King's chambers 
without being noticed, and escape as well!

248
00:19:53,460 --> 00:19:57,000
If we're found by the army now, 
we won't have a prayer of winning.

249
00:19:57,550 --> 00:20:00,880
If it comes down to it, 
at least we have my magic!

250
00:20:00,880 --> 00:20:02,980
Not that that reassures me much.

251
00:20:02,980 --> 00:20:04,250
What was that for?

252
00:20:04,250 --> 00:20:07,540
This whole plan hinges 
on my Gemini, remember?

253
00:20:07,540 --> 00:20:08,120
Sure, yeah.

254
00:20:08,380 --> 00:20:09,730
Happy, let's go.

255
00:20:10,880 --> 00:20:11,570
Aye!

256
00:20:16,330 --> 00:20:16,950
Lucy!

257
00:20:17,150 --> 00:20:17,860
Lucy-san!

258
00:20:20,670 --> 00:20:21,760
What is this?

259
00:20:28,600 --> 00:20:29,520
I can't move!

260
00:20:40,790 --> 00:20:41,710
The army!

261
00:20:42,300 --> 00:20:44,610
Why are there so many in this tunnel?

262
00:20:46,080 --> 00:20:47,640
How did they find us?

263
00:20:51,020 --> 00:20:53,250
So, these are the wizards from Earthland?

264
00:20:58,940 --> 00:20:59,800
Erza!

265
00:21:05,190 --> 00:21:10,650
Are you really different people 
than Natsu Dragyon and Lucy Ashley?

266
00:21:11,790 --> 00:21:12,500
Take them.

267
00:21:12,680 --> 00:21:13,220
Yes, Ma'am!

268
00:21:17,410 --> 00:21:20,150
Erza, listen to me!

269
00:21:20,550 --> 00:21:21,250
Okay?

270
00:21:22,250 --> 00:21:23,100
Wendy!

271
00:21:23,960 --> 00:21:25,780
Natsu, Lucy!

272
00:21:35,090 --> 00:21:36,180
Exceeds...

273
00:21:44,450 --> 00:21:46,780
Welcome home, Exceeds.

274
00:21:48,900 --> 00:21:51,150
What is the meaning of this?

275
00:21:54,850 --> 00:21:58,080
Happy, Carla... What exactly did you...

276
00:21:59,110 --> 00:22:01,920
I thank you for leading the 
intruders into our custody.

277
00:23:56,120 --> 00:23:57,710
Take a look, Natsu!

278
00:23:57,710 --> 00:24:00,360
It's a Cat Kingdom! Upa~!

279
00:24:00,360 --> 00:24:02,010
Ooh, amazing!

280
00:24:02,010 --> 00:24:05,330
Which means, wait... Are there kingdoms 
for other kinds of animals, too?

281
00:24:05,330 --> 00:24:07,850
I wish I could go to the Fish Kingdom.

282
00:24:07,850 --> 00:24:10,030
That's paradise for a cat!

283
00:24:10,030 --> 00:24:13,510
I think if you ate fish in the Fish 
Kingdom, you'd be in big trouble.

284
00:24:14,530 --> 00:24:16,360
Next time: Extalia!

285
00:24:17,040 --> 00:24:19,520
For me, I'd like to go to the Dragon Kingdom.

286
00:24:19,520 --> 00:24:21,590
What would you do there?

287
00:24:21,590 --> 00:24:22,420
Eat them?

288
00:24:22,420 --> 00:24:24,020
As if!

